": "-0.37", "tone": "neg", "strong": true}, {"label": "Reliability", "value": "84%", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "Whether he scores MORE goals than the quality of his shots would predict \u2014 pure finishing talent. We take his goals minus the expected goals on every shot of his career, then trust it more the more he's shot (a 2,000-shot sample is real; a 200-shot hot streak isn't yet).", "method": "Goals minus expected over career shots, then regressed to the mean by sample size. A high-volume shooter earns a more confident read (higher reliability)."}}, "skills": {"hits60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Physicality rate", "value": "6.84 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Physicality", "summary": "Physicality is how often he throws a body check \u2014 counted straight from the NHL's play-by-play. He's logged 309 hits over his last 151 games (6.8 per 60 minutes on the ice), and the grade ranks that against other forwards.", "caveat": "Home-scorer count -- arena bias is real (some rinks record far more than others). Read big gaps as signal, small ones as noise."}, "blocks60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Shot blocking rate", "value": "3.50 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Shot blocking", "summary": "Shot blocking is how willing he is to get in a shooting lane \u2014 counted straight from the NHL's play-by-play. He's logged 158 blocked shots over his last 151 games (3.5 per 60 minutes on the ice), and the grade ranks that against other forwards.", "caveat": "Home-scorer count -- arena bias is real (some rinks record far more than others). Read big gaps as signal, small ones as noise."}, "takeaways60": {"receipts": [{"label": "Puck stripping rate", "value": "0.93 / 60", "tone": "neutral"}], "method": "Per-60 rate over 3 seasons (TOI-weighted), ranked vs same-position peers.", "label": "Puck str